{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d00b91fe-ce2f-4d0b-b6a2-de745865037c","content":"Here are the pod spec changes you need:\n\n**Environment variables** to add to your container:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"      # required for NativeAOT\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n```\n\n**Volume mount** so dumps survive container restarts and can be retrieved:\n\n```yaml\nvolumeMounts:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nAnd under `spec.volumes`:\n\n```yaml\nvolumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi       # adjust to your expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` is **required** for NativeAOT since the runtime doesn't bundle `createdump` — it won't find it automatically.\n- Use `MiniDumpType=4` (Full) for most debugging; use `2` (Heap) or `1` (Mini) if size is a concern.\n- Replace `emptyDir` with a `persistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod deletion.\n- Ensure the `createdump` binary has execute permission and the process has `SYS_PTRACE` capability — add it under `securityContext` if needed:\n\n```yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  capabilities:\n    add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9ffc02ee-4da6-4ed5-a658-671347d47f5b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` at `/opt/tools/createdump`.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dumps, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables automatic dump on crash\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` — dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — path/pattern for dump file\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` — points the runtime to the createdump tool at `/opt/tools/createdump`, since NativeAOT apps don't include it by default\n\nNow I need to show how to configure this in Kubernetes, which means setting the environment variable on the container and mounting a volume for the crash dumps themselves.","outputTokens":867},"id":"746d5798-5abe-4224-a3a9-75a5462450f5","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:56:10.652Z","parentId":"5f66f47d-0b78-493b-9c7d-371b6e5fff8a"}
